> We're nearing summer, but that doesn't mean we're ready to say goodbye to sweet peas, adorable baby carrots, and tender lettuces! This salad celebrates the best of early summer produce. Juicy pan-seared chicken and garlic croutons round out this hearty salad.

== Mustard-Chive Vinaigrette ==

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @chives{1/4%ounce}(minced), @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{1%tbsp}, and @shallot{1%tbsp}(minced). Whisk in a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Garlic Croutons ==

Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Bring a medium #pot{} of salted water to boil. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1%tbsp}. Peel and cut the @carrots{1} into sticks (as if you'd be dipping them in hummus!). Mince the chives. Chop the @romaine lettuce{1} into bite sized pieces. Quarter the @radishes{3}. Cut the @ciabatta bread{1} into ½-inch cubes. Place the cubes on a #baking sheet{} and toast in the oven for ~{5-7%minutes} until crispy and golden.

Heat @butter{2%tbsp} on medium heat in the same pot used for the vegetables. Once melted, add the garlic and stir to combine. Toss in the ciabatta cubes and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Pan-Seared Chicken ==

Place your hand on top of the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} and slice into the middle of the meat, parallel to the cutting board. Stop before cutting all the way through. Open the chicken up like a book and flatten with a #mallet{} or heavy bottomed pan. Repeat with the other chicken breast. Season on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the pan and cook for ~{3-5%minutes} per side, until cooked through. Set aside to rest.

== Blanched Vegetables ==

Blanch the carrots and peas: Add the carrots to the boiling water and cook for ~{4-6%minutes}, until crisp-tender. Add the @peas{4%ounce} for the last ~{2%minutes} of cooking. Drain the vegetables and rinse under very cold water.

== Assembly ==

Toss the lettuce, carrots, peas, radishes, and garlic croutons into the mustard-chive vinaigrette and toss to coat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Plate the summer vegetable salad then top with a piece of seared chicken. Enjoy!